parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the oxygen sensor can cause the vehicle to fail state emission inspections, leading to potential environmental hazards and costly repairs.
symptoms: causing the vehicle to fail state emission inspections
and may require rewiring of the entire system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause loss of vehicle control, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: causing the ABS light to come on and remain on
and may result in the simultaneous failure of several wheel sensors
and rear axle shaft bearing failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brakes can cause loss of vehicle control, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: causing a loss of stopping power and potentially leading to accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear seat belt buckle can lead to inadequate restraint of passengers, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The rear seat belt buckle does not latch or stay securely fastened
the male portion of the buckle does not fit into the female portion
the buckle feels loose or unstable
the buckle is difficult to operate.
